<!-- ABOUT CREATOR -->
<section class="about-section">
  <div class="about-container">
    <!-- Left: Creator Image -->
    <div class="about-image-container">
      <div class="about-image-frame"></div>
      {% if section.settings.creator_image %}
        <img src="{{ section.settings.creator_image | image_url: width: 800 }}" alt="{{ section.settings.creator_name }}" class="about-image">
      {% else %}
        <img src="https://lorijsmith.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/IMG_1725_Facetune_01-11-2021-09-16-13.jpg" alt="Lori J Smith" class="about-image">
      {% endif %}
      <div class="about-signature-card">
        <p class="about-signature-card-name">{{ section.settings.creator_name }}</p>
        <p class="about-signature-card-title">{{ section.settings.creator_title }}</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Right: Scrollable Story Content -->
    <div class="about-content">
      <div class="about-header">
        <p class="about-label">{{ section.settings.about_label }}</p>
        <h2 class="about-title">{{ section.settings.about_title }}</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="about-scroll-content custom-scrollbar">
        <p class="about-quote">"{{ section.settings.about_quote }}"</p>
        
        <p class="about-text">
          Around six years ago, my life began transitioning into a new season. This transition came through a series of events, such as - the kiddos were no longer under our roof - we sold our home, which I believed would be our forever home, to begin the building process - AND I closed my photography business. Then - I started working full time with my husband - AND to add one more crazy dynamic...we were alone for the first time in our marriage, as new empty nesters.
        </p>
        
        <p class="about-text">
          In years prior, when I was fully engaged and primarily focused on my family, I felt confident, energetic, solid and at peace. Like I've often shared, I knew that what mattered most was giving my kiddos a better start. This season, everything changed. I knew I was no longer operating in that sense of clarity and vision for where I was headed. I didn't know what mattered most. AND I was doing a lot of what I thought I 'should' be doing. It was clear it was getting the best of me. I needed to find a way to work through this season.
        </p>

        <p class="about-text emphasis">
          Overall, I was excited about these changes! I did not expect the downward spiral I was entering into.
        </p>

        <p class="about-text">
          I thought I had clarity on where I was headed. However, I was floundering. My health was fading, and by 2 pm every day, I felt anxious, stressed, unsure, needy, insecure, and T I R E D. I didn't recognize how unsettling this transition was until my body and emotions revealed it to me. Life changes can be telling if we decide to take notice. They have a way of exposing areas that need growth.
        </p>

        <p class="about-text">
          I have always enjoyed journaling my thoughts and prayers. I love calendars and planning, BUT it would be an understatement to say that I became an obsessive fan of planning my day with intention and determination to spend my time wisely. I changed many of my routines, habits, and ideas I had about the structure of my life.
        </p>

        <p class="about-text">
          Then, over the next year, I began studying and learning systems and concepts from the plethora of journals and planners I had on my shelves but never used. This helped me zero in on how to best tackle my day for my overall wellness. I researched and studied books about creating habits, systems, time management, and personal well-being.
        </p>

        <p class="about-text callout">
          The changes were healing. I restructured my days and developed healthy habits such as drinking 75 oz of water daily - consistently taking my supplements - creating better sleep habits - and working on daily movement and prayer. I felt like I was on the right track... There was just one secret. <strong>I still felt like something was off...</strong>
        </p>

        <p class="about-text">
          I was deep in the pool of productivity hacks, side hustles, BIG dreams, time blocking, and goals; yet, the most successful thing I had experienced in my life to this point was my family, faith, and overall health and wellness. I found that "success" by utilizing the complete opposite idea of what I was learning. I always knew what I desired for myself, my marriage, and my children. It was simple, and it was hard, but it was the desire of my heart.
        </p>

        <p class="about-text">
          Recognizing this truth inspired me to begin developing a system that allowed me to find truth for my next season and work through my journey while continuing to organize my schedule and thoughts purposefully. The journals I used often focused on individual areas like fitness or business. That wasn't going to work. I wanted a journal that would be personal, uncomplicated, and encompass my entire life - faith, health, finances, career, family, personal growth, etc.
        </p>

        <p class="about-text large">
          I needed it to GROW with me along the way.
        </p>

        <p class="about-text">
          That's how I came to create the Plan To GRO Journal system. Planning is exciting; it gives clarity and creates productivity. However, I will always need growth and, therefore, need to journal through that process. Have I discovered my 'what matters most' in this next season? I know this - I want to show up and 'give my best self' in every commitment I make.
        </p>
        
        <div class="about-text closing">
          <p>
            You can find me over here building a life that nourishes the best of who I am. I hope I can help you along in your journey, too!
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Fade effect at bottom -->
      <div class="about-fade"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <!-- Connection Arrow to Testimonials -->
  <div class="about-arrow">
    <p class="about-arrow-text">{{ section.settings.arrow_text }}</p>
    <svg class="about-arrow-icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="43" height="18" viewBox="0 0 43 18" fill="none" style="transform: rotate(90deg);"><path d="M0 9H42" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M33 18C33 10.5 42 9 42 9C42 9 33 7.5 33 0" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- TESTIMONIALS -->
<section class="testimonials-section">
  <div class="testimonials-container">
    <div class="testimonials-header">
      <h2 class="testimonials-title">
        {{ section.settings.testimonials_title_line1 }}<br>
        <span class="italic">{{ section.settings.testimonials_title_line2 }}</span>
      </h2>
    </div>
    <div class="testimonials-slider">
      <button class="testimonial-nav-btn testimonial-nav-btn--prev"><svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7" /></svg></button>
      <button class="testimonial-nav-btn testimonial-nav-btn--next"><svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" /></svg></button>
      <div class="testimonial-content">
        <div class="testimonial-quote-mark">"</div>
        <div id="testimonialSlider">
          {% for block in section.blocks %}
            {% if block.type == 'testimonial' %}
              <blockquote class="testimonial-card" {% unless forloop.first %}style="display:none"{% endunless %}>
                <p class="testimonial-text">"{{ block.settings.quote }}"</p>
                <cite class="testimonial-author">- {{ block.settings.author }}</cite>
              </blockquote>
            {% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="testimonial-dots">
        {% for block in section.blocks %}
          {% if block.type == 'testimonial' %}
            <div class="testimonial-dot{% if forloop.first %} active{% endif %}"></div>
          {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA SECTION -->
<section class="cta-section cta-section--v2">
  <div class="cta-container">
    <div class="cta-content">
      <h2 class="cta-v2-title">
        {{ section.settings.cta_title_line1 }} {{ section.settings.cta_title_line2 }}
      </h2>
      <p class="cta-v2-script font-script">{{ section.settings.cta_subtitle }}</p>
      <p class="cta-v2-body">{{ section.settings.cta_body | default: 'New here? Get your first journal free just pay shipping.' }}</p>
      <a href="#product-section" class="cta-btn">
        <span>{{ section.settings.cta_button_text }}</span>
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="43" height="18" viewBox="0 0 43 18" fill="none"><path d="M0 9H42" stroke="currentColor"></path><path d="M33 18C33 10.5 42 9 42 9C42 9 33 7.5 33 0" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linejoin="round"></path></svg>
      </a>
    </div>
    <div class="cta-image-container">
      <div class="cta-image-frame"></div>
      {%- if section.settings.cta_image -%}
        <img src="{{ section.settings.cta_image | image_url: width: 900 }}" alt="Authentic Living" class="cta-image">
      {%- else -%}
        <img src="https://lorijsmith.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Facetune_11-07-2022-16-57-16-1536x898.jpg" alt="Authentic Living" class="cta-image">
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FULL-WIDTH IMAGE BANNER -->
<section class="banner-strip">
  {%- if section.settings.banner_image -%}
    <img src="{{ section.settings.banner_image | image_url: width: 1920 }}" alt="{{ section.settings.banner_alt | default: 'Community' }}" class="banner-strip__img" loading="lazy">
  {%- else -%}
    <img src="https://lorijsmith.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/three-women-journals.jpg" alt="Community" class="banner-strip__img" loading="lazy">
  {%- endif -%}
</section>

